</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="141" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="141">
The name is a combination of two Latin words 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">brun</emphasis>
meaning dark and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">badius</emphasis>
meaning reddish brown, highlighting the distinguishable dark reddish brown color of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="141" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="141">
Known only from the type locality near Manaus, Brazil (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. Distribution map of Notionotus spp." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1109.80775.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/709492" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">15</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="141" type="life history">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Life history.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="141">
The only known specimens were collected along the margin of a stream (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Habitat of Notionotus spp. A Venezuela: Amazonas State, type locality and habitat of N. bifidus (collecting event AS- 08 - 080 b) B Venezuela: Bolivar State: Type locality and habitat of N. insignitus (collecting event AS- 08 - 058) C Guyana: Region 9: type locality and habitat of N. patamona (collecting event GY 13 - 0318 - 01 C) D Suriname: Kabalebo, habitat and type locality for N. bicolor (collecting event SR 19 - 0310 - 01 F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1109.80775.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/709489" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">12C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
